AGI - It has been awarded definitively to the Group of companies led by Acea Ambiente with Suez Italy, Kanadevia Inova, Vianini and Rmb the realization of the thermo-valorizer of Rome>, previewed in the industrial area of Santa Palomba>.
&nbsp;
The freeway came as a result of the technical validation of the project by the certification company in charge. Roma Capitale> and RenewRome>, the company that will manage the plant for the next 33 years, have also signed the concession contract. In the coming days will be initiated the single regional authorization procedure > (Paur) which will be managed by the commissarial structure and which will see the participation of all the competent authorities.
&nbsp;
The opening of the yards for the construction of the plant is planned by the summer. The new plant will be able to treat 600 thousand tons> a year of undifferentiated and non-recyclable waste and will be fed by railings. Thanks to an investment of 1 billion euros, the Capital can finally be sure of the outlets for waste disposal at a lower cost than the current one for transport in Italy or abroad.
&nbsp;
The radiator, inserted in the Waste Plan approved in 2023> which aims to achieve 70% of separate collection, reducing to zero the use of landfills, is designed to integrate functionally with the entire cycle of differentiation. The project includes the construction of a Circular Economy Park, an area equipped with research, coworking, a greenhouse, a public garden and a panoramic tower over 70 meters high.
&nbsp;
There will also be four auxiliary plants for the recovery of heavy ashes, a photovoltaic system, a district heating network and an experimental system for the capture of the Co. The technologies adopted, the most advanced currently existing, will ensure an extremely low environmental impact: emissions will be significantly lower than the limits set by European directives and Best Available Techniques (Bat) and pollution caused by road traffic.
&nbsp;
The plant will produce thermal and electrical energy (65 MW total) enough to feed about 200 thousand families and will allow the recovery of approximately 10 thousand tons of steel, 2 thousand aluminum and 1.600 copper each year. The intervention also represents an extraordinary opportunity for urban regeneration for the industrial area of Santa Palomba, with an improvement of accessibility, services and infrastructure.
&nbsp;
"With this award we take a decisive step forward to carry out a management of the cycle of autonomous waste >, modern and sustainable that Rome was waiting for too long," said the mayor of Rome Roberto Gualtieri.
"The radiator - it has added - together with the new network of plants for the recycling of organic fraction and paper and plastic, allows to overcome an inefficient and polluting system based on dumps and expensive transfers to distant plants. We are now in a position to achieve the differentiated collection targets, and to safely treat the residual fraction with cutting-edge technologies that reduce the environmental impact of the Rome waste cycle by more than 90%".
<h2> Committees, Santa Palomba area is inidonea</h2>
&nbsp;"Gualtieri spent seven and a half million of the Romans to buy Ama a land where the incinerator cannot be built as the area is inidonea". This is what the Union of Committees against the incinerator states in a note.
"Santa Palomba is to declare area at high risk of environmental crisis in terms of regional law n.13/2019, whose exclusive competences remain firmly in the head of the Lazio Region. The area is pristine - continues the note of the Union of Committees because Santa Palomba hosts in a few square kilometers four of the nineteen plants at risk of significant accident existing throughout the Lazio Region. Tomorrow we will make available to the Municipality of Pomezia the proposal of deliberation that starts the process for the declaration of area at high risk of environmental crisis. Procedure that is characterized according to article 2, paragraph 2, of law 13/2019 in order to be free of any discretionary assessment by the Lazio Region. The proposal will be delivered in the hands of the Mayor of Pomezia Veronica Felici on the occasion of the presentation of the Book the Incinerator of Rome a wrong choice that will be held on Saturday 10 May at the Odradek library of Pomezia. The Gualtieri projects on Santa Palomba - concluded by the Union of Committees against the incinerator - end today on the day when it announces the definitive award to the rope of companies guided by Acea".
